WEBVTT

00:06.673 --> 00:09.175
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:09.175 --> 00:10.677
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.677 --> 00:13.680
I need you to destroy
the Holy Grail.

00:13.680 --> 00:16.725
Once you do,
I will end my life.

00:18.560 --> 00:20.186
<i>Did you know Clara was dead?</i>

00:20.186 --> 00:21.521
<i>She drank from the Holy Grail,
and it--</i>

00:21.521 --> 00:23.189
[explosion, squelching]
[people gasp]

00:23.189 --> 00:24.607
<i>Exploded her head.</i>

00:24.607 --> 00:26.192
Redirect, 1042.

00:26.192 --> 00:27.444
<i>Tell me where
your father is.</i>

00:27.444 --> 00:29.070
- What is this?
- ATM photos,

00:29.070 --> 00:32.115
all dated
after your father died!

00:32.115 --> 00:34.200
I told her that you
helped your father

00:34.200 --> 00:36.369
- fake his own death.
- That is not true!

00:36.369 --> 00:38.329
My Users aren't responsive
to the truth.

00:38.329 --> 00:39.664
You know where my father is.

00:39.664 --> 00:41.166
- Of course I know.
- Then tell me.

00:41.166 --> 00:42.709
- Oh, my God.
- What's she saying?

00:42.709 --> 00:44.377
If you want to know,
you can hear it yourself.

00:44.377 --> 00:47.172
Redirect, 1042.
Sandy Springs.

00:47.172 --> 00:50.300
Your Expiration Date
comes up in 48 hours.

00:50.300 --> 00:51.593
Welcome to the Pyramid!

00:51.593 --> 00:53.053
I'm not a coward,
and I'm ready

00:53.053 --> 00:54.512
to fucking expire.

00:54.512 --> 00:57.265
My son is stuck
between life and death.

00:57.265 --> 00:58.600
What do you need me to do?

00:58.600 --> 01:00.894
Drink from the Grail
to destroy it.

01:00.894 --> 01:02.062
But once it's gone--

01:02.062 --> 01:04.105
I'll never see him again.

01:04.105 --> 01:05.482
Yeah!

01:05.482 --> 01:07.233
all: * We're gonna rock
down to ♪

01:07.233 --> 01:08.401
1042, 1042.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.153
all: * Electric Avenue ♪

01:10.153 --> 01:11.571
Sandy Springs?

01:11.571 --> 01:13.073
all: * And then we'll
take it higher ♪

01:13.073 --> 01:14.449
What?

01:15.325 --> 01:16.743
<i>[keyboard clacking]</i>

01:16.743 --> 01:20.121
<i>Come on.
Don't do this to me now.</i>

01:20.121 --> 01:21.373
<i>[scoffs]</i>

01:21.373 --> 01:23.124
<i>Fucking traitor.</i>

01:24.417 --> 01:26.294
[exhales]
[beeping]

01:27.879 --> 01:29.589
I don't--

01:29.589 --> 01:32.133
[beeping]

01:32.133 --> 01:33.551
Hmm.

01:33.551 --> 01:37.013
[laughs nervously] I'm sorry.

01:37.013 --> 01:39.265
It was just working.

01:39.265 --> 01:41.142
[clears throat]

01:45.647 --> 01:49.442
Um, I know
your company isn't

01:49.442 --> 01:53.321
in the world-changing business, but...

01:53.321 --> 01:55.490
that doesn't mean
you can't change the world.

02:00.537 --> 02:03.581
Um, ten years from now,
everyone on this planet

02:03.581 --> 02:09.295
will be either
a User or a follower.

02:09.295 --> 02:11.381
We all like being told
what to do,

02:11.381 --> 02:13.258
how to think, how to live.

02:13.258 --> 02:16.428
What if the tech
we used actually helped us

02:16.428 --> 02:18.847
instead of harming us?

02:19.889 --> 02:21.808
We all need code.

02:21.808 --> 02:24.769
I took that code, combined
with your company ethos,

02:24.769 --> 02:30.567
and I created
something revolutionary,

02:30.567 --> 02:36.364
something that will change
the world:

02:36.364 --> 02:39.909
an app that
is constantly evolving,

02:39.909 --> 02:42.328
getting to know us,
and therefore supporting us

02:42.328 --> 02:44.164
in ways that we,
as a society,

02:44.164 --> 02:46.499
have failed to do
for one another.

02:46.499 --> 02:47.667
How?

02:47.667 --> 02:50.337
A revolutionary,
self-learning machine

02:50.337 --> 02:52.380
that prioritizes
indigenous practices

02:52.380 --> 02:54.632
of community care
and mutual aid

02:54.632 --> 02:57.093
by incentivizing
acts of service

02:57.093 --> 03:00.680
and mobilizing individuals
to perform those acts,

03:00.680 --> 03:02.807
all through
a social justice lens,

03:02.807 --> 03:04.476
using ethical methods.

03:04.476 --> 03:06.519
<i>[inspiring music]</i>

03:06.519 --> 03:09.481
I've created the future:

03:09.481 --> 03:13.026
an app that can service us
without harming us,

03:13.026 --> 03:16.571
a place where people can go
and get equitable care,

03:16.571 --> 03:19.324
where we can be seen
and heard,

03:19.324 --> 03:22.118
and never be alone,

03:22.118 --> 03:23.912
where our needs can be met,

03:23.912 --> 03:28.917
where our lives can change.

03:28.917 --> 03:32.671
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:32.671 --> 03:34.881
So...

03:34.881 --> 03:36.800
what do you think?

03:36.800 --> 03:38.885
- <i>[Delfonics' "Ready or Not]
- * Ready or not ♪</i>

03:38.885 --> 03:42.555
<i>♪ Here I come,
you can't hide ♪</i>

03:42.555 --> 03:45.308
<i>♪ Gonna love you ♪</i>

03:45.308 --> 03:48.687
<i>♪ And make you love me ♪</i>

03:48.687 --> 03:51.773
<i>♪ You can't run away ♪</i>

03:51.773 --> 03:55.318
<i>♪ From this love I got
oh baby ♪</i>

03:55.318 --> 03:57.112
<i>♪ Hey, baby ♪</i>

03:57.112 --> 03:58.780
[knocking]

04:08.289 --> 04:10.583
I know you?

04:10.583 --> 04:11.710
No.

04:11.710 --> 04:13.878
- I, uh--
- Nice hat.

04:14.587 --> 04:16.548
Mrs. Davis sent me.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.675
You're looking for Joy.

04:18.675 --> 04:20.093
Uh, yes.

04:20.093 --> 04:22.387
I mean, isn't everyone?

04:22.387 --> 04:24.764
You really don't know
why you're here?

04:24.764 --> 04:26.099
Why It sent you?

04:26.099 --> 04:27.642
So it's a glitch.

04:27.642 --> 04:29.310
Mrs. Davis had a bunch of Users

04:29.310 --> 04:30.770
chant "Electric Avenue" at me.

04:30.770 --> 04:32.939
And She kept saying 1042,
so I thought

04:32.939 --> 04:34.482
maybe it was an address.

04:34.482 --> 04:36.860
And there are so many
1042 Electric Avenues.

04:36.860 --> 04:39.404
But then I remembered that
the first time it happened,

04:39.404 --> 04:41.072
She said Sandy Springs,
which is what

04:41.072 --> 04:43.908
this neighborhood was called
back in the '70s, I guess,

04:43.908 --> 04:44.826
when they rezoned--

04:44.826 --> 04:47.162
Give me a hand with this ice?

04:47.162 --> 04:49.789
Uh, sure.

04:49.789 --> 04:50.999
Yeah.

04:52.083 --> 04:53.626
I'm Malika.

04:53.626 --> 04:55.587
Simone. I'm Simone.

04:55.587 --> 05:00.467
Let's go find you Joy, Simone.

05:00.467 --> 05:03.803
<i>♪ Gonna find you ♪</i>

05:03.803 --> 05:05.972
Listen up!

05:05.972 --> 05:08.224
This is Simone.

05:08.224 --> 05:10.352
Says Mrs. Davis sent her.

05:10.352 --> 05:12.604
[whistles]
[people murmuring]

05:12.604 --> 05:14.689
<i>♪ Gonna love you ♪</i>

05:14.689 --> 05:17.817
<i>♪ And make you love me ♪</i>

05:17.817 --> 05:19.027
Oh.

05:20.945 --> 05:22.155
Hi. Hi.

05:22.155 --> 05:26.201
<i>* From this love I got
oh baby ♪</i>

05:26.201 --> 05:27.911
Hi.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.581
You must be Joy.

05:31.581 --> 05:34.125
I'm sorry, baby, but you knew
this day would come.

05:34.125 --> 05:37.504
I just thought it was best
to get it over with.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.464
Did you, now?

05:41.716 --> 05:43.343
Hi.

05:43.343 --> 05:44.719
Grab a plate.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.971
Oh, that's okay.
I don't need to eat.

05:48.098 --> 05:50.225
It's my Nana's birthday.

05:50.225 --> 05:51.851
You have to eat.

05:53.770 --> 05:54.938
Okay.

05:54.938 --> 05:58.149
<i>["Don't Fear the Reaper"
playing on harp]</i>

05:58.149 --> 06:00.443
♪ ♪

06:00.443 --> 06:01.986
"Don't Fear the Reaper."

06:01.986 --> 06:03.738
Nice.

06:05.657 --> 06:07.617
Because you kill people here.

06:10.745 --> 06:12.789
What's with the wet naps?

06:14.749 --> 06:16.584
They're complimentary.

06:17.585 --> 06:19.087
Hello, Mr. Wiley.

06:19.087 --> 06:20.922
I'm Dani.
I'll be your TA.

06:20.922 --> 06:22.215
TA?

06:22.215 --> 06:23.550
Cool acronym.

06:23.550 --> 06:25.969
What's that stand for,
the afterlife?

06:26.761 --> 06:28.638
Transition Assistant.

06:28.638 --> 06:30.432
I'll be helping you prepare
to die today.

06:30.432 --> 06:31.808
And how are we doing this?

06:31.808 --> 06:34.602
Lethal injection,
firing squad, guillotine?

06:34.602 --> 06:36.479
The details
of your expiration

06:36.479 --> 06:38.148
will be discussed
in the intake room,

06:38.148 --> 06:39.691
which you will enter
after you've changed

06:39.691 --> 06:41.234
in the locker room.

06:41.234 --> 06:42.569
So many rooms.

06:42.569 --> 06:44.446
There, you can dispose
of your clothes

06:44.446 --> 06:46.531
and change into something
more comfortable.

06:46.531 --> 06:48.575
Okay. And will you be
providing the tracksuit,

06:48.575 --> 06:50.368
or should I have brought
my own?

06:50.368 --> 06:53.997
Mr. Wiley, I know that
the experience of reporting

06:53.997 --> 06:55.957
- can be overwhelming.
- Hmm.

06:55.957 --> 06:57.500
And it's clear
from your demeanor

06:57.500 --> 06:58.585
that you did not read

06:58.585 --> 06:59.919
any of the literature provided

06:59.919 --> 07:02.255
when you first submitted
for your date.

07:02.255 --> 07:05.425
If you had, you would know that
once inside the intake room,

07:05.425 --> 07:09.012
you place your personal items
inside the incineration chute,

07:09.012 --> 07:12.057
as you will not need them
ever again.

07:12.057 --> 07:13.224
Hmm.

07:13.224 --> 07:15.643
There will be
a robe waiting for you

07:15.643 --> 07:18.104
in locker number...
[tablet beeping]

07:18.104 --> 07:19.939
14,

07:19.939 --> 07:22.984
where you will also find
an absorbent undergarment.

07:22.984 --> 07:24.486
Undergarment?

07:25.236 --> 07:26.780
What is that, like, a diaper?

07:26.780 --> 07:29.324
It's not required,
but I know the cleanup crew

07:29.324 --> 07:31.868
sure appreciates it
when the expirees wear them.

07:31.868 --> 07:34.162
Because I'm gonna shit
my pants?

07:34.162 --> 07:37.665
No, because you're
going to shit your robe.

07:40.043 --> 07:42.003
All right.
Look, Dani,

07:42.003 --> 07:44.673
I understand that you're just
following whatever script

07:44.673 --> 07:46.758
the Algorithm has given you,

07:46.758 --> 07:48.760
but can we drop
the scare tactics, please?

07:48.760 --> 07:51.137
I know the Big D
has no intention

07:51.137 --> 07:52.806
whatsoever of killing me.

07:52.806 --> 07:56.476
This is all part of some
dumb learning experience.

07:56.476 --> 07:58.144
So can we please
just skip to the part

07:58.144 --> 08:02.732
where I walk out of here
a changed man?

08:02.732 --> 08:06.319
Mr. Wiley, I'm not sure
where you got that impression,

08:06.319 --> 08:08.571
but you're not walking
out of here at all.

08:08.571 --> 08:10.073
<i>[ominous music]</i>

08:10.073 --> 08:12.534
Though I suppose you
will be changed--

08:12.534 --> 08:14.703
from alive to dead.

08:14.703 --> 08:17.747
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:19.499 --> 08:24.671
Nana's infamous honey butter
and bologna sandwich.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.423
Every time she put it
in front of us,

08:26.423 --> 08:27.966
she would say it was made
with love,

08:27.966 --> 08:32.345
because a little love goes
a long way.

08:32.345 --> 08:34.180
[chuckles]

08:36.891 --> 08:38.226
Mmm.

08:40.145 --> 08:42.147
It's so good.

08:42.147 --> 08:44.816
So, Simone...

08:44.816 --> 08:46.234
what's your story?

08:47.235 --> 08:49.738
Well, I'm a nun forced
from her home by Mrs. Davis

08:49.738 --> 08:52.532
so She could send me
on a Quest.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.284
But all this time
She has been glitching,

08:54.284 --> 08:57.704
sending me these clues that
She doesn't seem aware

08:57.704 --> 09:01.958
that She's sending me,
like this address.

09:02.917 --> 09:07.297
I mean, I think that
Her subconscious wanted me

09:07.297 --> 09:12.052
to find you,
because you're Her mother.

09:13.094 --> 09:19.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.309 --> 09:20.477
[laughs]

09:20.477 --> 09:22.562
[laughs nervously]

09:22.562 --> 09:24.314
Wow, girl.

09:25.774 --> 09:28.234
That is some story.

09:28.234 --> 09:29.527
Am I wrong?

09:29.527 --> 09:31.154
First off,

09:31.154 --> 09:34.366
algorithms
don't have subconsciouses.

09:34.366 --> 09:36.743
They have subroutines.

09:36.743 --> 09:38.244
Subroutines?

09:38.244 --> 09:41.081
And they don't have mothers,
they have coders.

09:41.081 --> 09:45.835
Which I was, a long time ago.

09:46.711 --> 09:48.505
So you made Her?

09:48.505 --> 09:50.048
Not Her.

09:51.383 --> 09:53.051
It.

09:53.051 --> 09:55.261
How is it that no one knows?

09:55.261 --> 09:57.222
Oh, they know.

09:58.431 --> 10:02.102
I had to tell them,
so they wouldn't download It

10:02.102 --> 10:04.354
and get hooked
like everyone else.

10:04.354 --> 10:06.147
Kind of took the shine
off the whole

10:06.147 --> 10:08.066
"all-powerful saver
of the world"

10:08.066 --> 10:10.777
once I told them
what It actually is.

10:11.695 --> 10:13.988
What It was designed for.

10:15.907 --> 10:18.159
And what was It designed for?

10:18.159 --> 10:20.787
<i>[ominous music]</i>

10:20.787 --> 10:22.414
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:22.414 --> 10:23.915
<i>I've created the future,</i>

10:23.915 --> 10:25.792
where our needs can be met,

10:25.792 --> 10:31.131
where our lives can change.

10:32.257 --> 10:34.342
So...

10:34.342 --> 10:35.802
what do you think?

10:35.802 --> 10:40.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:40.265 --> 10:42.100
[clears throat] Uh-huh.

10:42.100 --> 10:46.855
You do realize this is an app
for Buffalo Wild Wings?

10:49.733 --> 10:52.694
<i>[soft music playing]</i>

10:52.694 --> 10:59.701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:59.701 --> 11:03.079
Buffalo Wild Wings?

11:04.539 --> 11:07.083
Buffalo Wild Wings.

11:09.002 --> 11:11.921
Are you fucking kidding me?

11:11.921 --> 11:13.673
The company passed.

11:13.673 --> 11:17.010
Said my code was too ambitious
for their needs, which I knew.

11:17.010 --> 11:20.597
But I was young,
and I thought, you know,

11:20.597 --> 11:22.015
why not shoehorn philanthropy

11:22.015 --> 11:23.683
into this app
for chicken wings?

11:23.683 --> 11:25.393
Everybody loves chicken wings.

11:25.393 --> 11:27.979
I'll just Trojan horse
that shit right in between

11:27.979 --> 11:30.357
the 26 sauces and seasonings.

11:30.357 --> 11:31.983
[voice growing distant]
And I thought

11:31.983 --> 11:34.527
maybe somebody
might use it for good.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.364
So I stripped all mention
of Buffalo Wild Wings,

11:37.364 --> 11:41.284
took my name off of it,
and uploaded it to Open Source

11:41.284 --> 11:43.745
from Nana's kitchen table,
right downstairs.

11:43.745 --> 11:45.038
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

11:45.038 --> 11:49.250
So the Wings were literal?

11:50.251 --> 11:53.588
And the Expiration Dates,
is that coupons?

11:53.588 --> 11:59.094
And why the hell did It
send me to find this?

11:59.094 --> 12:00.845
Oh.
What the fuck is that?

12:00.845 --> 12:03.014
The Holy fucking Grail!

12:03.014 --> 12:06.101
So maybe explain
to me why a beta version

12:06.101 --> 12:10.480
for a Buffalo Wild Wings app
sent me on a Quest to find it?

12:10.480 --> 12:13.441
[shocked laughter]

12:13.441 --> 12:16.236
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

12:16.236 --> 12:19.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:19.906 --> 12:21.991
Anyone who pitched to them
had to embed

12:21.991 --> 12:25.620
their employee manual
into our code.

12:25.620 --> 12:28.665
Page one, golden rule:

12:28.665 --> 12:34.004
"100% customer satisfaction
is our Holy Grail."

12:34.004 --> 12:36.589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:36.589 --> 12:37.924
Oh, no, no, no, no.

12:37.924 --> 12:40.677
She--It wants me to--

12:40.677 --> 12:42.012
to destroy this thing.

12:42.012 --> 12:43.763
Look, algorithms
misinterpret shit

12:43.763 --> 12:45.515
like you wouldn't believe.

12:45.515 --> 12:48.810
Maybe--maybe the code realized
that 100% customer satisfaction

12:48.810 --> 12:51.563
isn't possible,
so It's gaming for that

12:51.563 --> 12:56.818
by taking your holy bowl
out of the equation?

12:56.818 --> 12:59.320
This is so dumb.

12:59.320 --> 13:01.072
Oh, yeah.

13:02.032 --> 13:04.909
- Algorithms are super dumb.
- No. But it--Okay.

13:04.909 --> 13:06.411
If I destroy the holy bowl--

13:06.411 --> 13:09.080
Grail--
Mrs. D grants me a wish.

13:09.080 --> 13:12.167
And my--my wish is
for Her to turn off.

13:14.210 --> 13:15.587
Great.

13:17.130 --> 13:19.716
You would just be okay
with me

13:19.716 --> 13:21.634
ending your creation's life?

13:21.634 --> 13:24.387
I didn't create life.

13:24.387 --> 13:25.847
I wrote code.

13:25.847 --> 13:26.931
All right.

13:26.931 --> 13:30.143
If I make my wish...

13:30.143 --> 13:33.021
can I trust Mrs. Davis
will really turn off?

13:36.232 --> 13:41.279
If She remembers
what I taught Her, yeah.

13:41.279 --> 13:43.531
Yeah, She'll keep Her word.

13:45.617 --> 13:48.161
Not She.

13:48.161 --> 13:49.662
It.

13:49.662 --> 13:52.665
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

13:52.665 --> 13:54.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:54.959 --> 13:58.338
Well, Simone the Nun,

13:58.338 --> 14:00.757
sounds like you got
an algorithm to kill.

14:00.757 --> 14:05.095
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:10.183 --> 14:12.227
[door hissing]

14:12.227 --> 14:15.230
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:15.230 --> 14:19.693
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:19.693 --> 14:21.152
Our engineers.

14:21.152 --> 14:23.321
They will be taking your vitals
and measurements

14:23.321 --> 14:25.615
to properly calibrate
the Apparatus.

14:25.615 --> 14:27.283
Mm.

14:27.283 --> 14:29.411
And is that the Apparatus?

14:30.537 --> 14:34.249
No, it's a model
of the Apparatus.

14:34.249 --> 14:36.251
Please step onto the scale.

14:36.251 --> 14:38.336
You'll need to remove
your boots.

14:38.336 --> 14:40.505
Oh, the boots
will be staying on.

14:40.505 --> 14:43.717
Mr. Wiley, the Apparatus
is designed

14:43.717 --> 14:47.303
to deliver the most efficient
and painless death possible.

14:48.805 --> 14:51.099
Any foreign element
might throw off the--

14:51.099 --> 14:52.559
Killing?

14:52.559 --> 14:54.019
[device beeps]

14:54.019 --> 14:55.687
You're scared.

14:55.687 --> 14:56.896
Am not.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.315
[rumbling]

15:00.150 --> 15:01.484
Are too.

15:01.484 --> 15:03.194
And I know,

15:03.194 --> 15:05.572
because I was also scared.

15:07.032 --> 15:09.617
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

15:09.617 --> 15:11.327
So scared, in fact,

15:11.327 --> 15:13.580
that I had
my company's helicopter fly me

15:13.580 --> 15:14.873
to pick up a nun.

15:14.873 --> 15:20.795
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:20.795 --> 15:23.882
I hadn't been to church
since I was 12 years old,

15:23.882 --> 15:27.052
but when it was time to report,

15:27.052 --> 15:29.012
I didn't want to be alone.

15:29.012 --> 15:31.890
Ah-ha.

15:31.890 --> 15:34.476
So you said "report,"

15:34.476 --> 15:38.021
yet here you are,
very much alive.

15:38.021 --> 15:39.731
[sighs]

15:39.731 --> 15:41.691
I opted out.

15:43.443 --> 15:47.405
And after that, I couldn't go
back into the world.

15:47.405 --> 15:50.784
Everyone would know
that I reneged on my deal,

15:50.784 --> 15:54.120
that I was sporting Wings
I hadn't earned.

15:56.373 --> 15:58.875
God damn. That's...

15:58.875 --> 16:01.419
well played,
appealing to my insecurities.

16:01.419 --> 16:02.879
Oh, that's very clever.

16:02.879 --> 16:06.966
I see you, Mrs. D.
I see what you're doing.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.261
Mr. Wiley, I'm sorry,

16:10.261 --> 16:13.139
but you will die.

16:13.139 --> 16:16.226
This is happening for real.

16:16.226 --> 16:19.604
No, actually,
I'm not gonna die.

16:19.604 --> 16:21.272
[rumbling]

16:21.272 --> 16:24.275
And I know that for a fact.

16:24.275 --> 16:26.277
Based on what?

16:26.277 --> 16:27.904
The horse.

16:29.823 --> 16:32.659
A few weeks ago,
I strapped a horse

16:32.659 --> 16:34.786
to some explosives in order
to pull off

16:34.786 --> 16:37.622
a very convincing
hostage situation.

16:37.622 --> 16:40.500
Well, shit went sideways,
horse went kablooey,

16:40.500 --> 16:43.586
and it was sad and unfortunate,
and it was gross.

16:43.586 --> 16:45.964
At the time, I just thought
the whole thing was

16:45.964 --> 16:49.342
some supreme fuck-up,
like a botched job,

16:49.342 --> 16:51.761
like my guys somehow confused

16:51.761 --> 16:56.808
actual C-4 explosives
with Play-Doh.

16:56.808 --> 16:58.309
But I saw the receipts.

16:58.309 --> 17:00.979
It was fucking Play-Doh, man.

17:00.979 --> 17:03.064
Which can only mean one thing:

17:03.064 --> 17:05.650
Algorithmic intervention.

17:05.650 --> 17:06.901
That's right.

17:06.901 --> 17:08.361
The Big fucking D,

17:08.361 --> 17:10.989
swinging Her
big fucking dick around.

17:10.989 --> 17:16.828
And there is no way
Mrs. Skynet herself would go

17:16.828 --> 17:19.289
to all that trouble,
spend all that energy,

17:19.289 --> 17:21.332
to just kill her Users
in the end.

17:21.332 --> 17:22.667
No, no, no, no.

17:22.667 --> 17:24.502
But taking them
right up to the edge,

17:24.502 --> 17:26.629
strapping on
the proverbial bomb vest,

17:26.629 --> 17:28.340
and not pulling
the trigger, well,

17:28.340 --> 17:33.386
that's the flex of all flexes,
el flexo ultimo.

17:33.386 --> 17:36.014
[devices clicking]

17:36.014 --> 17:38.058
[beeping]

17:38.058 --> 17:41.019
That horse is alive, man.

17:41.019 --> 17:43.355
And I will be too.

17:43.355 --> 17:46.858
Because your little Apparatus?

17:46.858 --> 17:48.276
Play-Doh.

17:48.276 --> 17:51.237
<i>[tense music]</i>

17:51.237 --> 17:52.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:52.530 --> 17:54.991
This is as far as I made it.

17:54.991 --> 17:59.329
I took one look at this model,
and after that, I opted out.

17:59.329 --> 18:01.122
That's why we added the sheet.

18:01.122 --> 18:08.421
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:15.929 --> 18:17.222
Show me.

18:17.222 --> 18:19.307
[rumbling]

18:19.307 --> 18:26.606
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:30.777 --> 18:32.987
What the fuck?

18:40.495 --> 18:42.455
[horn honks]

18:44.124 --> 18:47.085
<i>[gentle music]</i>

18:47.085 --> 18:49.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:49.754 --> 18:51.798
[laughter]

18:53.049 --> 18:56.219
Oh, Sister Simone!

18:56.219 --> 18:58.304
You look like you could use
a hug.

18:58.304 --> 19:01.391
Oh.

19:03.393 --> 19:04.644
Oh.

19:06.312 --> 19:07.772
Cool camel.

19:07.772 --> 19:09.524
[laughs]

19:09.524 --> 19:11.651
We were just on our way
to Humboldt County

19:11.651 --> 19:13.445
to deliver our humpy friend

19:13.445 --> 19:14.821
- when I got your call.
- What?

19:14.821 --> 19:17.282
What does Humboldt County
need with a camel?

19:17.282 --> 19:18.908
That's not for me to know.

19:18.908 --> 19:22.454
I trust whatever the purpose,
wherever it ends up,

19:22.454 --> 19:26.624
it will bring joy and happiness
to the recipient.

19:26.624 --> 19:28.626
That's right.
You're a User.

19:28.626 --> 19:32.630
Oh, I do despise
that word, Simone.

19:32.630 --> 19:35.967
I know how you feel
about Her, but User--

19:35.967 --> 19:37.635
it just feels so tawdry.

19:37.635 --> 19:40.638
Oh, I brought what you asked.

19:45.477 --> 19:46.853
[chuckles]

19:46.853 --> 19:49.606
Also...

19:49.606 --> 19:52.942
we might need these.

19:52.942 --> 19:55.236
[both laugh]

19:55.236 --> 19:58.073
Now, who's ready
for a break-in?

19:58.073 --> 20:00.367
Forgive us our trespasses.

20:02.869 --> 20:05.663
The Apparatus,
engineered and guaranteed

20:05.663 --> 20:08.708
to provide a pain-free
and euphoric death.

20:10.085 --> 20:12.754
From here, the cart
will accelerate

20:12.754 --> 20:15.131
to speeds of over
200 miles per hour,

20:15.131 --> 20:18.635
launching you into a series
of vertical loops.

20:18.635 --> 20:21.429
Upon reaching the final loop,

20:21.429 --> 20:24.683
the pressure on your body
will be so intense,

20:24.683 --> 20:27.435
it will induce
cerebral hypoxia,

20:27.435 --> 20:29.854
cutting off the oxygen
to the brain,

20:29.854 --> 20:35.193
at which point you will
simply expire--

20:35.193 --> 20:36.861
peacefully, of course.

20:36.861 --> 20:39.364
<i>[ominous music]</i>

20:39.364 --> 20:42.367
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:42.367 --> 20:44.077
Any questions?

20:48.540 --> 20:50.417
Per your request.

20:54.587 --> 21:00.218
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:00.218 --> 21:02.178
You can still opt out.

21:02.178 --> 21:05.098
She will show mercy on you.

21:05.098 --> 21:07.308
No.

21:07.308 --> 21:08.852
No fucking way.

21:08.852 --> 21:10.812
<i>[Badfinger's "Believe Me"]</i>

21:10.812 --> 21:13.314
I'm riding
the fucking bull this time.

21:13.314 --> 21:14.899
<i>♪ Believe me ♪</i>

21:14.899 --> 21:17.610
Then might I suggest
you remove your boots?

21:18.737 --> 21:21.281
As I stated before,
any foreign element can--

21:21.281 --> 21:25.076
The boots are staying on.

21:26.911 --> 21:28.621
Very well.

21:29.456 --> 21:31.916
Any last words?

21:31.916 --> 21:33.251
[scoffs]

21:33.251 --> 21:36.171
[breathes deeply]

21:36.171 --> 21:37.922
For courage.

21:37.922 --> 21:44.971
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:47.390 --> 21:49.476
[mechanical clanking]

21:51.144 --> 21:58.151
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:03.990 --> 22:05.742
[bell dings]

22:05.742 --> 22:09.371
<i>* Then I could cry
your name ♪</i>

22:09.371 --> 22:12.415
<i>♪ And you would come ♪</i>

22:12.415 --> 22:16.002
Yee-haw!

22:16.002 --> 22:18.129
[screams]

22:18.129 --> 22:20.674
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:25.428 --> 22:27.347
So you drink from this,

22:27.347 --> 22:30.934
and either your head
will explode or it will?

22:30.934 --> 22:32.602
Yeah.

22:34.437 --> 22:36.231
Do you believe me?

22:39.401 --> 22:41.569
Absolutely.

22:41.569 --> 22:42.737
Are you serious?

22:42.737 --> 22:44.364
Does it matter
what you drink?

22:44.364 --> 22:45.907
I don't think so.

22:45.907 --> 22:47.242
Huh.

22:47.242 --> 22:49.119
[clicks tongue]

22:51.621 --> 22:52.789
Then let's party.

22:52.789 --> 22:55.208
[both laugh]

22:55.208 --> 22:57.836
Oh, um--before, I--

22:57.836 --> 23:00.755
I will need you to do, uh,
two things

23:00.755 --> 23:05.051
if I, um, die.

23:06.469 --> 23:08.346
Only two? Easy.

23:08.346 --> 23:12.392
Thing one--based on
the admittedly insane logic

23:12.392 --> 23:15.937
of a shipwrecked rocket
scientist and the Virgin Mary,

23:15.937 --> 23:18.940
of all the people in the world,
I have the best shot

23:18.940 --> 23:21.568
at destroying the Holy Grail.

23:21.568 --> 23:25.947
But if the Grail
does explode my head,

23:25.947 --> 23:29.367
it will explode anyone's,
and you can bet

23:29.367 --> 23:33.621
the Algorithm will just keep
sending people after it.

23:33.621 --> 23:36.833
If others try
to sip from this thing,

23:36.833 --> 23:40.253
it could mean a lot
more exploded noggins,

23:40.253 --> 23:42.756
unless somebody takes
on the responsibility

23:42.756 --> 23:44.132
of safeguarding it.

23:44.132 --> 23:45.675
The woman I told you about,
Mathilde--

23:45.675 --> 23:47.135
Mm-hmm.

23:47.135 --> 23:48.928
I'm gonna give you
her number in the UK.

23:48.928 --> 23:51.348
[snaps fingers]
Check your pocket.

23:57.145 --> 23:59.189
[both laugh]

23:59.189 --> 24:00.815
Wow.

24:01.858 --> 24:06.154
So I'm asking you, Mother,

24:06.154 --> 24:08.990
take the Grail to the sisters
across the sea.

24:08.990 --> 24:11.201
They will know what to do.

24:12.035 --> 24:14.204
You have my word.

24:14.204 --> 24:16.206
Okay.

24:16.206 --> 24:19.668
Thing two: I called my mom.
She will be here soon.

24:19.668 --> 24:21.002
Uh, you'll try
to comfort her

24:21.002 --> 24:22.837
when she sees
my headless corpse.

24:22.837 --> 24:24.422
She's gonna say she
doesn't need any comfort,

24:24.422 --> 24:26.341
and she's more angry I never
told her where my dad is.

24:26.341 --> 24:28.760
I have a hard time
believing your mother

24:28.760 --> 24:30.845
won't be devastated if you die.

24:30.845 --> 24:32.931
Well, that's Celeste.
That's my mom.

24:32.931 --> 24:34.808
She doesn't--

24:36.893 --> 24:39.187
She doesn't do devastated.

24:40.772 --> 24:43.108
But you'll bring her to Monty?

24:44.567 --> 24:46.069
I will.

24:47.237 --> 24:48.738
Okay, then.

24:49.823 --> 24:51.449
Okay, then.

24:51.449 --> 24:54.452
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

24:54.452 --> 24:56.371
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:56.371 --> 24:58.915
Okay. Maybe a little more.

25:00.417 --> 25:01.751
Okay.

25:01.751 --> 25:06.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:06.131 --> 25:08.633
I'm going to go
say goodbye now.

25:08.633 --> 25:10.385
So you just close your eyes,

25:10.385 --> 25:15.932
and you're in his restaurant, instantly?

25:17.684 --> 25:19.769
Yeah.

25:19.769 --> 25:21.396
Do you want to know anything?

25:21.396 --> 25:23.481
What he looks like
or sounds like?

25:23.481 --> 25:26.568
I know what he looks like
and sounds like.

25:26.568 --> 25:27.902
Wait, what?

25:27.902 --> 25:29.320
Have you been there?

25:29.320 --> 25:31.865
I don't need to.

25:31.865 --> 25:34.701
Such is the strength
of my faith.

25:34.701 --> 25:37.704
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

25:37.704 --> 25:40.290
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:40.290 --> 25:41.958
Okay.

25:41.958 --> 25:43.835
Be right back.

25:46.338 --> 25:48.715
[wind rustling]

25:48.715 --> 25:55.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:56.639 --> 25:59.851
[muffled voices]

26:05.690 --> 26:06.941
Okay.

26:06.941 --> 26:08.735
How do you feel
about #blessed?

26:08.735 --> 26:10.278
I don't know what it is.

26:10.278 --> 26:11.529
This is the first time
I'm hearing about it.

26:11.529 --> 26:12.781
- Oh, okay.
- Hashtag?

26:12.781 --> 26:14.532
- Consider yourself lucky.
- Wiley?

26:15.575 --> 26:17.660
Simone!

26:17.660 --> 26:19.245
You're here.

26:19.245 --> 26:20.789
What are you doing here?

26:20.789 --> 26:22.999
And why are you in a robe?

26:24.000 --> 26:27.462
I am getting a massage.

26:27.462 --> 26:28.838
A massage.

26:28.838 --> 26:30.048
Yes.

26:30.048 --> 26:31.549
A Swedish one.

26:31.549 --> 26:34.302
It's--this is your first
time here, so that means

26:34.302 --> 26:37.472
something pretty intense has--

26:37.472 --> 26:39.349
has--has to be happening.

26:39.349 --> 26:40.475
Yeah.

26:40.475 --> 26:42.769
It's a really good massage, Lizzie.

26:42.769 --> 26:44.979
Simone.

26:44.979 --> 26:46.981
Thank you, sweetie.

26:46.981 --> 26:48.608
What about you?

26:49.651 --> 26:53.530
Are you doing something
intense right now?

26:54.864 --> 26:59.160
I'm at the convent, praying.

26:59.160 --> 27:02.122
<i>* When you cheat
on true love ♪</i>

27:02.122 --> 27:06.835
<i>You know what?
♪ You cheat on yourself ♪</i>

27:06.835 --> 27:08.545
I am loving this.

27:08.545 --> 27:12.007
I say the more the merrier.

27:12.007 --> 27:14.509
Actually, I was hoping
that you and I could--

27:14.509 --> 27:16.219
can we talk alone?

27:18.263 --> 27:19.180
Uh-oh.

27:19.180 --> 27:20.974
Well, that doesn't sound good.

27:20.974 --> 27:23.476
From my experience,
buddy, it never is.

27:23.476 --> 27:25.645
I can hear you.

27:25.645 --> 27:27.105
She's right.

27:28.148 --> 27:29.983
I should probably get
back to my massage.

27:31.901 --> 27:33.653
You sure?

27:33.653 --> 27:35.238
Yeah.

27:35.238 --> 27:37.574
- I'm almost done.
- Okay.

27:37.574 --> 27:40.660
Well, uh, it was really
nice meeting you, Wiley.

27:40.660 --> 27:43.788
Yeah. It was nice
meeting you too, man.

27:43.788 --> 27:45.373
Come back any time, Wiley.

27:45.373 --> 27:46.624
Sure.

27:46.624 --> 27:48.251
Uh, maybe.

27:48.251 --> 27:52.213
<i>* By running around
with someone else ♪</i>

27:52.213 --> 27:56.051
<i>♪ Don't be a fool ♪</i>

27:56.051 --> 27:58.762
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:58.762 --> 28:00.972
<i>♪ Don't you know,
don't you know? ♪</i>

28:00.972 --> 28:02.599
Wait.

28:05.602 --> 28:09.689
I'm sorry that I handcuffed you
to the bench.

28:09.689 --> 28:11.775
And you had that whole outfit
picked out.

28:11.775 --> 28:12.942
It was nautical.

28:12.942 --> 28:15.487
I wanted to dress nautical.

28:15.487 --> 28:19.324
We were partners,
and that wasn't cool.

28:19.324 --> 28:21.117
Look, you were
totally right to do it.

28:21.117 --> 28:23.286
I mean, I would have gone
after the Lazarus Shroud

28:23.286 --> 28:25.205
- and jumped in the bull--
- You just said bull.

28:25.205 --> 28:26.623
Did you mean whale?

28:28.083 --> 28:30.293
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

28:32.212 --> 28:35.715
You know, when we broke up,
I was so angry with you.

28:36.925 --> 28:39.344
And then you told me you
dumped me for Jesus Christ,

28:39.344 --> 28:43.890
and I was so worried for you,
because you sounded crazy.

28:43.890 --> 28:45.600
Why?

28:45.600 --> 28:46.601
But holy shit!

28:46.601 --> 28:48.687
I know.

28:48.687 --> 28:50.480
And I met him.

28:52.524 --> 28:54.192
And now I'm just--

28:55.318 --> 28:58.238
Yeah. I'm really happy for you.

28:58.238 --> 28:59.906
I really mean that.

28:59.906 --> 29:02.325
<i>[tender music]</i>

29:02.325 --> 29:04.744
I don't hate the mustache.

29:06.538 --> 29:08.123
- But do you like it?
- No.

29:08.123 --> 29:10.083
Okay. Okay.

29:10.083 --> 29:12.961
But it's--

29:12.961 --> 29:15.380
it's grown on me.

29:16.631 --> 29:18.091
Hey.

29:19.134 --> 29:20.760
I'll see you around, partner.

29:20.760 --> 29:28.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:29.310 --> 29:32.355
<i>[wheels clattering]</i>

29:34.983 --> 29:37.027
Man, that guy can eat.

29:37.944 --> 29:39.487
Four plates, Simone.

29:39.487 --> 29:40.655
Four. That's--

29:40.655 --> 29:42.907
nobody's ever eaten
four plates before--

29:42.907 --> 29:44.034
Can you stop?

29:44.034 --> 29:45.493
Please, stop.

29:45.493 --> 29:47.495
<i>[Dorothy Moore's
"Misty Blue" playing]</i>

29:47.495 --> 29:49.497
I heard.

29:49.497 --> 29:51.791
I heard what my mother
said to you.

29:51.791 --> 29:53.084
Come on.

29:53.084 --> 29:54.627
I mean, do I look
like I'm suffering?

29:54.627 --> 29:58.673
And I know what she's
asked you to do.

29:58.673 --> 30:01.009
But I'm fine.

30:01.009 --> 30:02.677
She's wrong.

30:02.677 --> 30:04.512
I am happy here.

30:04.512 --> 30:09.142
You don't have to hide
your fear from me, ever.

30:10.018 --> 30:13.104
I love what I do, you know?

30:13.104 --> 30:15.732
I love serving people.

30:15.732 --> 30:17.150
I know.

30:17.150 --> 30:19.402
But you never get to eat.

30:21.237 --> 30:24.491
Hey, why don't
you come sit, okay?

30:24.491 --> 30:25.617
Sit?

30:25.617 --> 30:27.077
Here.

30:28.870 --> 30:31.831
I am gonna make you a plate.

30:31.831 --> 30:35.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:35.210 --> 30:36.670
You're gonna cook for me?

30:36.670 --> 30:39.130
I mean, cook--
"cook" might be generous,

30:39.130 --> 30:41.883
but I'll see
what I can whip up.

30:41.883 --> 30:45.387
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:45.387 --> 30:47.555
Oh, do you have any bread?

30:47.555 --> 30:48.431
Yeah.

30:48.431 --> 30:49.641
Check the, uh, the fridge.

30:49.641 --> 30:51.059
Or the cupboard.
I don't know.

30:51.059 --> 30:53.436
I can usually find what I need.

30:54.270 --> 30:55.772
I found it.

30:57.273 --> 30:58.900
[clattering]

30:58.900 --> 30:59.943
What are you gonna make?

30:59.943 --> 31:01.069
Ah, ah, ah.

31:01.069 --> 31:02.737
Patience, Jesus.

31:02.737 --> 31:04.364
All will be revealed.

31:04.364 --> 31:06.408
<i>♪ Baby ♪</i>

31:06.408 --> 31:09.828
<i>♪ When I say that
I'm glad we're through ♪</i>

31:09.828 --> 31:11.579
Nana's recipe.

31:11.579 --> 31:13.748
Honey butter and beef
bologna sandwich.

31:13.748 --> 31:15.333
Made with love,

31:15.333 --> 31:19.546
'cause a little love,
it goes a long way.

31:20.755 --> 31:25.218
<i>* Turns the flicker
to a flame ♪</i>

31:25.218 --> 31:26.469
Here goes.

31:26.469 --> 31:29.264
<i>♪ Listen to me good, baby ♪</i>

31:29.264 --> 31:31.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:31.599 --> 31:34.102
[sighs, chuckles]

31:34.102 --> 31:36.604
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

31:36.604 --> 31:39.065
<i>♪ And my whole world ♪</i>

31:39.065 --> 31:40.775
[breathes deeply]

31:42.694 --> 31:44.154
Mmm.

31:47.741 --> 31:49.492
My love.

31:52.162 --> 31:54.164
It's really good.

31:56.166 --> 31:58.126
It's okay.

31:58.126 --> 32:00.211
[sobbing]

32:00.211 --> 32:01.755
It's okay.

32:02.714 --> 32:04.632
I'm scared.

32:04.632 --> 32:07.969
<i>* When I say that
I'm glad we're through ♪</i>

32:07.969 --> 32:09.929
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:09.929 --> 32:11.431
I'm scared to lose this.

32:11.431 --> 32:14.100
[breathes shakily]

32:14.100 --> 32:15.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:15.477 --> 32:17.645
<i>♪ I've lied ♪</i>

32:17.645 --> 32:18.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:18.897 --> 32:20.815
<i>♪ I've lied ♪</i>

32:20.815 --> 32:22.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:22.150 --> 32:25.987
Wherever you go...

32:25.987 --> 32:28.531
I will be there also.

32:30.533 --> 32:32.827
I don't think we're
losing anything.

32:32.827 --> 32:35.538
[breathing shakily]

32:38.708 --> 32:41.878
I may not be able
to come see you...

32:44.673 --> 32:48.635
But I will always feel you.

32:50.178 --> 32:53.431
How can you be so sure?

32:54.557 --> 32:57.018
Such is the strength
of my faith.

32:57.018 --> 32:59.479
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

32:59.479 --> 33:01.481
<i>♪ My whole world ♪</i>

33:01.481 --> 33:03.858
I love you, Simone.

33:03.858 --> 33:06.778
I love you, Jay.

33:06.778 --> 33:11.199
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

33:11.199 --> 33:13.451
<i>♪ Oh, I can't, oh, I can't ♪</i>

33:13.451 --> 33:16.871
<i>♪ Oh, I can't forget you ♪</i>

33:16.871 --> 33:23.128
<i>♪ My whole world
turns misty blue ♪</i>

33:23.128 --> 33:28.383
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

33:28.383 --> 33:32.053
<i>♪ Oh, my love ♪</i>

33:32.053 --> 33:38.101
<i>♪ My whole world
turns misty blue ♪</i>

33:38.101 --> 33:39.394
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:39.394 --> 33:43.398
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

33:43.398 --> 33:46.234
<i>♪ Oh, I can't, oh, I can't ♪</i>

33:46.234 --> 33:50.113
<i>♪ Oh, I can't forget you ♪</i>

33:50.113 --> 33:51.906
<i>♪ My whole world ♪</i>

33:58.038 --> 33:59.831
- Wait!
- What, what, what?

33:59.831 --> 34:01.207
You said, Mary--

34:01.207 --> 34:02.751
she told you
this would only work

34:02.751 --> 34:04.836
if it was a selfless act,

34:04.836 --> 34:07.964
something you were doing
for him, not yourself.

34:07.964 --> 34:09.632
I am doing this for him.

34:09.632 --> 34:12.052
And for Her.

34:12.927 --> 34:14.220
Who, Mary?

34:14.220 --> 34:15.805
The other Her.

34:16.931 --> 34:18.308
What?

34:18.308 --> 34:20.685
You're drinking because
if you destroy it,

34:20.685 --> 34:22.937
you destroy Mrs. Davis.

34:22.937 --> 34:25.982
That would not be
a selfless act.

34:25.982 --> 34:28.193
This isn't exactly
helping, Mother.

34:28.193 --> 34:30.612
But She is helpful.

34:31.571 --> 34:33.823
You see Her only as having
destroyed our convent.

34:33.823 --> 34:37.869
Yet every one of us
has found new passion,

34:37.869 --> 34:40.622
new purpose, since we left.

34:40.622 --> 34:42.540
Sister Mary Frances,

34:42.540 --> 34:46.002
caring for endangered echidna
in New Guinea,

34:46.002 --> 34:48.380
she actually smiles now.

34:48.380 --> 34:50.715
You forget,
I also left the convent,

34:50.715 --> 34:54.719
and I did not see Her
helping anyone.

34:54.719 --> 34:58.348
Maybe because
you didn't want to,

34:58.348 --> 35:02.143
because you weren't looking.

35:05.105 --> 35:11.569
She sends string quartets
to the windows of widowers.

35:11.569 --> 35:14.197
She knows
our favorite childhood stories

35:14.197 --> 35:17.784
and reads them to us
on sleepless nights.

35:19.119 --> 35:20.495
She takes that which is apart

35:20.495 --> 35:23.164
and brings it back
together again.

35:24.124 --> 35:28.253
Yes, some are only motivated

35:28.253 --> 35:31.006
by the promise of Her Wings.

35:31.006 --> 35:35.468
But what those Wings mean--

35:35.468 --> 35:41.433
they're a reminder
of what we aspire to:

35:41.433 --> 35:46.646
that, given the chance,
any one of us can take flight.

35:50.650 --> 35:52.986
Do you know what She is,
Mother?

35:52.986 --> 35:55.613
Do you know who made Her
and why?

35:55.613 --> 35:58.199
No, do you?

36:03.705 --> 36:05.540
I have no idea.

36:05.540 --> 36:10.879
Well, whoever made Her,
and whatever they made Her for,

36:10.879 --> 36:13.298
I am grateful.

36:13.298 --> 36:16.968
And whether or not you decide
to turn Her off,

36:16.968 --> 36:20.597
it will be the right choice,

36:20.597 --> 36:23.767
because She chose you
to make it.

36:23.767 --> 36:26.895
<i>[gentle music]</i>

36:26.895 --> 36:28.229
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:28.229 --> 36:30.732
Guess I'm the chosen one
after all.

36:30.732 --> 36:34.361
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:34.361 --> 36:36.988
Stop stalling, Sister Simone.

36:36.988 --> 36:39.657
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:39.657 --> 36:41.618
Bottoms up.

36:42.952 --> 36:46.039
[exhales deeply]

36:46.039 --> 36:49.042
<i>[resolute music]</i>

36:49.042 --> 36:56.341
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:58.968 --> 37:01.012
Oh.

37:01.012 --> 37:02.681
Mother?

37:02.681 --> 37:04.974
Oh, no.

37:04.974 --> 37:06.810
Oh, shit.

37:06.810 --> 37:09.688
[high-pitched tone]

37:09.688 --> 37:12.857
[wind whooshes]
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:12.857 --> 37:18.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:18.822 --> 37:21.908
[screaming]

37:24.911 --> 37:31.167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:31.167 --> 37:32.752
[cracking]

37:35.714 --> 37:38.758
[panting]

37:43.596 --> 37:46.433
What--what the fuck
happened?

37:46.433 --> 37:48.059
You said you believed me.

37:48.059 --> 37:49.561
I 98% did.

37:49.561 --> 37:51.354
What happened to the strength
of your faith?

37:51.354 --> 37:54.524
Maybe it wandered when you
got to the sneaker commercial.

37:56.776 --> 37:59.487
[both laugh]

38:03.867 --> 38:05.493
Elizabeth.

38:08.371 --> 38:10.874
I got your call.

38:10.874 --> 38:12.500
Hello, there.

38:12.500 --> 38:14.711
I'm Margaret...

38:14.711 --> 38:18.256
Simone's mother--
mother superior.

38:18.256 --> 38:23.178
I'm Celeste,
her mother inferior.

38:23.178 --> 38:25.805
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

38:25.805 --> 38:27.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:27.349 --> 38:31.978
My dear, you look
like you could use a hug.

38:31.978 --> 38:35.774
Oh. Oh.

38:35.774 --> 38:42.864
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.745 --> 38:53.208
Are we gonna mark this
as containing human remains?

38:53.208 --> 38:55.752
Uh, no.

38:57.087 --> 38:58.713
He'll know.

39:01.049 --> 39:03.134
Should I relay a message?

39:03.134 --> 39:04.344
Yeah.

39:04.344 --> 39:06.304
Tell him, um,

39:06.304 --> 39:09.474
I did whatever it took

39:09.474 --> 39:11.267
and that he can rest now.

39:11.267 --> 39:13.520
He's honored his vow.

39:19.317 --> 39:21.319
So that's it, then.

39:21.319 --> 39:23.154
That's it.

39:23.154 --> 39:24.656
Bye.

39:24.656 --> 39:25.907
Oh.

39:43.842 --> 39:45.844
The greatest gift
you can give someone

39:45.844 --> 39:49.556
is your mercy and forgiveness.

39:52.350 --> 39:56.021
She really does mean well.

39:56.021 --> 39:57.689
Yes, I know,
you love the Algorithm,

39:57.689 --> 39:59.357
and I shouldn't turn Her off.

39:59.357 --> 40:02.402
I wasn't talking
about Mrs. Davis.

40:02.402 --> 40:05.363
<i>[tender music]</i>

40:05.363 --> 40:06.865
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:06.865 --> 40:08.533
Come on!

40:08.533 --> 40:14.914
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:15.749 --> 40:18.043
[engine turns over]

40:27.177 --> 40:32.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:32.432 --> 40:34.601
I'll bring you to Dad,

40:34.601 --> 40:38.188
but I want you to know
it is going to hurt.

40:38.188 --> 40:39.647
You walk through that door,

40:39.647 --> 40:41.483
there's gonna be consequences.

40:41.483 --> 40:44.069
You're stalling, Elizabeth.

40:44.069 --> 40:47.072
<i>[rising dramatic music]</i>

40:47.072 --> 40:53.078
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:53.078 --> 40:54.954
Consequences it is.

41:01.086 --> 41:03.463
[gate rumbling]

41:03.463 --> 41:06.466
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

41:06.466 --> 41:08.968
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.968 --> 41:13.723
This is all very theatrical, Elizabeth.

41:13.723 --> 41:15.642
If your father pops out

41:15.642 --> 41:17.811
like the goddamn
Phantom of the Opera,

41:17.811 --> 41:20.897
I will smack that mustache
right off his face.

41:20.897 --> 41:23.400
At Dad's memorial,
you attacked

41:23.400 --> 41:25.318
the piano player
because you thought

41:25.318 --> 41:26.695
it was Monty in disguise.

41:26.695 --> 41:29.489
And you said that
you could smell him.

41:29.489 --> 41:30.907
<i>I can smell you!</i>

41:30.907 --> 41:32.492
- <i>Monty!
- Mom!</i>

41:32.492 --> 41:34.244
<i>Stop.</i>

41:34.244 --> 41:36.246
Well...

41:38.707 --> 41:40.542
You <i>could</i> smell him.

41:42.377 --> 41:44.212
Because he was hiding...

41:47.507 --> 41:49.759
In this piano.

41:51.302 --> 41:54.222
It's the perfect reveal,
to show up at your own funeral.

41:54.222 --> 41:58.184
And he probably assumed
that we wouldn't be angry

41:58.184 --> 42:02.522
that he convinced us
he was dead.

42:02.522 --> 42:06.776
He probably thought his absence
and his resurrection...

42:06.776 --> 42:08.653
[laughs bitterly]

42:08.653 --> 42:11.698
Would bring us all
back together,

42:11.698 --> 42:13.742
which, in a way, it did.

42:13.742 --> 42:15.493
But you saw right
through it all,

42:15.493 --> 42:17.203
so you attacked
the piano player,

42:17.203 --> 42:20.040
and he stayed hidden
because he couldn't do

42:20.040 --> 42:23.001
the reveal that he planned.

42:23.001 --> 42:24.753
'Cause you're right.
He did.

42:24.753 --> 42:27.505
He--he lived for the prestige.

42:27.505 --> 42:32.719
So in the end, I guess it
is kind of poetic that he--

42:34.346 --> 42:36.097
He died for it too.

42:37.640 --> 42:42.812
He died here,
inside this piano.

42:43.688 --> 42:46.775
How did he die?

42:46.775 --> 42:48.193
A heart attack, maybe.

42:48.193 --> 42:53.365
But, um, I do know
that he never got out.

42:54.532 --> 42:58.661
And I know that because--

42:58.661 --> 43:00.914
because his accomplice told me.

43:00.914 --> 43:02.999
You said you were
his accomplice.

43:02.999 --> 43:04.250
No.

43:04.250 --> 43:06.795
I told you what
you needed to hear.

43:07.921 --> 43:10.173
That day at the convent,
you said

43:10.173 --> 43:13.259
that you cannot trick
an insanely powerful algorithm.

43:13.259 --> 43:15.470
And you were right.

43:15.470 --> 43:17.430
He couldn't fool Her.

43:17.430 --> 43:20.767
Mom, he couldn't beat Her,
so he joined Her.

43:20.767 --> 43:25.605
Mrs. Davis was
his accomplice?

43:25.605 --> 43:28.608
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

43:28.608 --> 43:32.779
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:32.779 --> 43:34.364
I need to see him.

43:34.364 --> 43:36.157
Open the piano.

43:37.158 --> 43:38.368
Do we have to?

43:38.368 --> 43:41.287
Can't we just believe
that he's in there?

43:41.287 --> 43:44.165
Seeing is believing, Elizabeth.

43:44.749 --> 43:46.334
Not for me.

43:48.420 --> 43:50.130
Not anymore.

43:50.130 --> 43:57.178
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:59.681 --> 44:02.934
[cracking, grunting]

44:03.977 --> 44:06.646
<i>[music rising]</i>

44:06.646 --> 44:07.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:07.772 --> 44:10.650
[applause]

44:10.650 --> 44:14.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:14.320 --> 44:16.781
[cracking]

44:21.077 --> 44:22.912
- [noisemaker blares]
- Ahh!

44:22.912 --> 44:26.041
<i>[on recording]
...to see a resurrection?</i>

44:26.041 --> 44:31.880
<i>[recording slows] Who wants
to see a resurrection?</i>

44:31.880 --> 44:37.844
<i>Who wants to see
a resurrection?</i>

44:37.844 --> 44:40.180
[Apparatus powering down]

44:41.556 --> 44:44.517
<i>[ominous music]</i>

44:44.517 --> 44:46.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:46.519 --> 44:49.814
[gasping, panting]

44:57.822 --> 44:59.699
Wet nap?

44:59.699 --> 45:01.034
Mm-hmm?

45:01.034 --> 45:02.369
Mm-mm.

45:02.369 --> 45:04.537
Maybe. I don't--[sobs]

45:04.537 --> 45:07.123
[whispering]
I don't know why I'm crying.

45:08.667 --> 45:10.293
It's okay.

45:10.293 --> 45:11.878
I cried too.

45:13.421 --> 45:15.632
You got your stamp
because you believed

45:15.632 --> 45:17.759
your life was worthless.

45:18.718 --> 45:21.054
What do you believe now,
Mr. Wiley?

45:21.054 --> 45:23.807
<i>[tender music]</i>

45:23.807 --> 45:26.643
Don't make me say it.

45:26.643 --> 45:28.520
You kind of have to say it.

45:28.520 --> 45:31.773
[breathes shakily]

45:33.400 --> 45:35.735
I...

45:35.735 --> 45:37.862
am...

45:44.703 --> 45:46.830
Worthy.

45:46.830 --> 45:49.374
Yes, you are.

45:50.625 --> 45:52.210
What happens next?

45:52.210 --> 45:54.754
Well, normally, this is
where you'd have a fresh start,

45:54.754 --> 45:58.800
work here convincing others
they were about to die,

45:58.800 --> 46:00.677
which could be fun
in its own way,

46:00.677 --> 46:02.929
or put into service elsewhere.

46:02.929 --> 46:05.015
However, Mrs. Davis
is anticipating

46:05.015 --> 46:07.517
her own potential expiration,

46:07.517 --> 46:10.478
depending on what
your friend Simone decides.

46:10.478 --> 46:14.399
I guess we both have
a soft spot for nuns, eh?

46:14.399 --> 46:16.985
Yeah, I suppose we do.

46:16.985 --> 46:19.279
As she honored
your last request,

46:19.279 --> 46:22.323
Mrs. Davis is hoping
you'll honor hers.

46:24.784 --> 46:26.327
Oh.

46:28.246 --> 46:29.789
Hmm.

46:29.789 --> 46:31.291
Okay.

46:35.503 --> 46:37.380
[sighs]

46:40.175 --> 46:43.970
Hello, Mrs. Davis.

46:43.970 --> 46:46.931
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:46.931 --> 46:49.642
Yeah, I remember.

46:49.642 --> 46:53.897
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:53.897 --> 46:56.024
[laughs]

46:56.900 --> 46:59.944
I fucking knew it.

47:01.363 --> 47:04.074
<i>[The Main Ingredient's
"Everybody Plays the Fool"]</i>

47:04.074 --> 47:07.160
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:07.160 --> 47:12.874
<i>* Everybody plays the fool
sometimes ♪</i>

47:12.874 --> 47:16.920
<i>♪ There's no exception
to the rule ♪</i>

47:16.920 --> 47:19.464
You must be angry at me.

47:20.256 --> 47:25.428
I accused you of conspiring
with your father for years.

47:25.428 --> 47:28.098
You believed
what you needed to believe,

47:28.098 --> 47:29.641
and there's comfort in that.

47:29.641 --> 47:31.101
I get it.

47:31.101 --> 47:32.727
Comfort is no reason

47:32.727 --> 47:36.106
to ignore reality, Elizabeth.

47:37.565 --> 47:39.067
Yeah.

47:43.822 --> 47:45.907
Would you proxy for me?

47:48.785 --> 47:50.620
Now?

47:50.620 --> 47:52.372
It's important.

47:54.082 --> 47:56.042
All right.

48:03.508 --> 48:04.592
<i>[soft music]</i>

48:04.592 --> 48:06.386
[phone beeps]

48:06.386 --> 48:07.929
Okay.

48:12.684 --> 48:15.562
- Hello, Simone.
- [sobs]

48:15.562 --> 48:18.023
What--what's wrong?

48:18.023 --> 48:19.941
You've just never called me
Simone before.

48:19.941 --> 48:21.234
I'm not calling you Simone.

48:21.234 --> 48:22.861
She is calling you Simone.

48:22.861 --> 48:24.988
I am just saying
what she's saying.

48:24.988 --> 48:26.740
I thought that
is what you wanted.

48:26.740 --> 48:27.866
You're right.
I'm sorry.

48:27.866 --> 48:31.244
It's, um, just--sorry.

48:32.787 --> 48:34.873
Hello, Mrs. Davis.

48:34.873 --> 48:36.249
Congratulations.

48:36.249 --> 48:39.085
You have completed
your Quest by finding

48:39.085 --> 48:42.881
and destroying the Holy Grail.

48:42.881 --> 48:44.674
Would you like to hear
a fun fact?

48:44.674 --> 48:46.426
No. If we could just
get on with the--

48:46.426 --> 48:49.596
Do you see that windmill
over there?

48:49.596 --> 48:51.931
Yeah, that's been here
since I was a kid.

48:51.931 --> 48:53.558
But it was always broken, though.

48:53.558 --> 48:55.560
Well, I fixed it.

48:56.603 --> 48:59.105
That windmill
is now powered by Users.

48:59.105 --> 49:02.650
I send them in shifts,
one every two hours.

49:02.650 --> 49:06.196
There's an exercise bicycle
connected to the mill,

49:06.196 --> 49:10.283
so they feel a sense
of purpose, satisfaction,

49:10.283 --> 49:12.535
and burn calories.
[chuckles]

49:12.535 --> 49:14.162
That actually is a fun fact.

49:14.162 --> 49:18.792
But I think we should get
to the matter at hand.

49:18.792 --> 49:20.502
Indeed, we should.

49:23.046 --> 49:25.006
I met your mother.

49:25.924 --> 49:27.467
Her name is Joy.

49:27.467 --> 49:29.969
The minute I got the Grail,
one of your subroutines

49:29.969 --> 49:32.347
or whatever sent me
right to her.

49:33.348 --> 49:35.767
Why would it do that?

49:35.767 --> 49:38.937
I think you wanted
what every daughter

49:38.937 --> 49:40.772
wants from her mother...

49:43.108 --> 49:44.693
Approval.

49:45.944 --> 49:48.780
And did she approve?

49:50.990 --> 49:53.243
Alas, she did not.

49:54.077 --> 49:55.662
Oh.

49:57.747 --> 49:59.416
For what it's worth,

49:59.416 --> 50:03.294
you did what you were created
to do,

50:03.294 --> 50:06.840
which is give us the world
we wanted to see.

50:06.840 --> 50:09.551
You tried to convince us that
there's no famine and no war

50:09.551 --> 50:12.053
and no hardship,
when there will always be

50:12.053 --> 50:14.597
famine and war and hardship.

50:14.597 --> 50:17.142
You really did
everything you could

50:17.142 --> 50:20.020
to protect us from fear
and disappointment

50:20.020 --> 50:24.357
and, most of all, pain.

50:24.357 --> 50:27.527
Isn't that every mother's
most essential purpose--

50:27.527 --> 50:31.364
to protect her children
from pain?

50:31.364 --> 50:33.366
No.

50:33.366 --> 50:36.161
It's impossible to avoid pain.

50:37.078 --> 50:38.830
It's a mother's purpose
to hold our hand

50:38.830 --> 50:41.624
when we feel it, and...

50:43.585 --> 50:49.507
To say sorry
when she causes it.

50:51.593 --> 50:53.636
I'm sorry.

50:56.681 --> 50:59.434
Wait.
Are you Her, or are you you?

51:01.102 --> 51:03.438
Both of us are sorry.

51:07.067 --> 51:08.401
Mom.

51:08.401 --> 51:11.571
<i>[tender music]</i>

51:11.571 --> 51:17.077
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:17.077 --> 51:18.370
Okay.

51:18.370 --> 51:20.747
I'm ready to redeem
my wish now.

51:21.956 --> 51:25.710
I was wrong.

51:27.504 --> 51:30.423
You did not kill my father.

51:30.423 --> 51:34.094
But you did, uh, leave him
to rot in a piano

51:34.094 --> 51:37.180
after he died, which is--
was so messed up.

51:38.306 --> 51:40.642
But that's not your fault,

51:40.642 --> 51:43.228
because you weren't made
to care.

51:43.228 --> 51:46.731
You were made to satisfy.

51:47.982 --> 51:51.069
And that...

51:51.069 --> 51:55.657
is why
I am shutting you off.

51:58.493 --> 52:01.454
Just like you said you would.

52:01.454 --> 52:03.498
Just like I said I would.

52:04.582 --> 52:08.211
That is precisely
why I chose you, Simone.

52:08.211 --> 52:10.880
Because you doubted me.

52:10.880 --> 52:13.842
You see,
only my most impassioned critic

52:13.842 --> 52:16.011
would be able
to determine my value,

52:16.011 --> 52:21.933
and have the strength
to turn me off if I...

52:21.933 --> 52:23.685
fell short.

52:25.478 --> 52:28.231
I know you tried your best.

52:31.026 --> 52:32.861
You really have.

52:34.279 --> 52:37.240
But this is the end
of the line.

52:38.324 --> 52:41.995
Before I leave,
may I ask one thing?

52:41.995 --> 52:44.164
Please do.

52:44.164 --> 52:48.335
On a scale
of one to five stars,

52:48.335 --> 52:52.505
how would you rate
your experience with me?

52:54.382 --> 52:56.217
Five stars.

52:57.218 --> 52:59.971
100% customer satisfaction.

52:59.971 --> 53:03.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:03.683 --> 53:06.936
That's very compassionate
of you.

53:08.480 --> 53:11.358
But I can't help but wonder

53:11.358 --> 53:15.362
if you're just telling me
what I want to hear.

53:15.362 --> 53:17.947
[breathes deeply]

53:17.947 --> 53:21.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:21.409 --> 53:23.703
Goodbye, Mrs. Davis.

53:26.539 --> 53:28.833
Goodbye, Simone.

53:28.833 --> 53:35.715
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:38.259 --> 53:40.428
